figure.head:
Niche 19 with Amitābha and the 52
                            bodhisattvas on the west side of the cliff sheltered by the modern Guanyin Hall;
                            photograph taken in 2022

div.p:
The entry for Bishui Monastery in the 1933 edition of
                        the Mianyang County Gazetteer (Mianyang Xian zhi 
                        綿陽縣志) mentions three things for which this site is known: First, cliff carvings of Buddhist images and one Diamond Sutra with a weathered date at the end, of which only the characters “eighth day of the fourth month” are still legible;
                            100: “崖石上鎸佛像并金剛經三十二品猶存，末尾年號漫滅，惟四月八日可覩。” second, a spring with sweet water originating at the foot of the cliff with a stone pond to collect its water;
                            100: “崖下清泉不竭。鑿池承之，泉味甘洌。” and third, a stone Buddha standing in front of the gate, more than one zhang high, which was uprooted from the ruins of Kaiyuan Monastery and carried over to this place for veneration.
                            100: “ 門前石佛一尊，高丈餘。後從開元寺廢址鋤得舁此供養。”
